<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iranian Oil Minister Signs Agreements, Departs </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1305105194 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 13 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1305105194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Our country's oil minister yesterday, on the second 
day of his visit to South Korea, met with heads of building 
companies and commercial firms and oil refinery managers. In 
the course of these meetings, the possibility of cooperation 
with South Korea's oil companies and commercial firms in the 
fields of importing natural gas and liquified petroleum gas from 
Iran and their participation at the oil, gas, and petrochemical 
projects in the Persian Gulf were investigated, and it was 
agreed to exchange expert delegations in this connection. 
  During the meeting between Mr. Aqazadeh and heads of the 
Korean firms, some memoranda of understanding were exchanged. 
  The oil minister and his accompanying delegation left South 
Korea for Kuala Lumpur today. 

</TEXT>

