<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials Fired for Agricultural Boycott </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials Fired for Agricultural Boycott </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK0705041794 Seoul YONHAP in English 0339 GMT 7 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK0705041794 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 7 (YONHAP) -- Agriculture, Forestry and 
Fisheries Minister Choe In-ki sacked three officials Saturday, 
holding them responsible for the trouble caused by the recently 
introduced law on the distribution and price stabilization of 
agro-fishery products. 
  The three are Sin Sun-u, director-general of the 
Agricultural 
Marketing Bureau, Kim Chu-su, chief of the Planning and Budget 
Division, and Choe Pu-kwan, of the Market and Price Policy 
Division, according to the spokesman. 
  The three officials failed to devise measures to ensure the 
law's smooth execution and, therefore, took responsibility for 
the trouble in which thousands of middlemen at the Karak 
Agro-Fishery Wholesale Market paralyzed the distribution system 
by boycotting their business in protest against the revised law 
banning wholesale activities by middlemen, the spokesman said. 
  The three will lose their jobs unless they are reinstated 
within three months. 
  In a statement, Minister Choe instructed all ministry 
officials to develop agro-fishery industries, warning that he 
would severely punish those who fail to perform their jobs well. 

</TEXT>

