<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Group Formed To Aid Koreans Fleeing DPRK </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Group Formed To Aid Koreans Fleeing DPRK </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1005103494 Seoul YONHAP in English 0642 GMT 10 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1005103494 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 10 (YONHAP) -- A civil organization was 
formed Tuesday to support North Koreans who have fled to China 
or who are working as loggers in Siberia. 
  The "Headquarters of Movement for Helping Brethren Fleeing 
North Korea" was officially inaugurated in a founding rally 
attended by nearly 300 persons including lawyer O Chae-to, Chong 
Nam-yol, president of the Association of Protestant Orders, and 
Song Won-yong, a former lawmaker, at Kodang (Cho Man-sik) 
Memorial Hall in central Seoul. 
  The group said, "North Koreans who fled to China to avoid 
human rights suppression and adversities and North Korean 
loggers in Siberia do not receive any adequate protection from 
the Chinese Government and the Russian Government, let alone the 
South Korean Government. 
  "It's about time we, citizens, began a pan-national movement 
to bring them and help them settle here." 
  The organization said it will begin with a fact-finding 
survey of the North Koreans in flight in Russia and China, ask 
the Russian and Chinese Governments to provide humanitarian 
assistance to them and start gathering funds to held them settle 
here. 

</TEXT>

