<H3> <TI>   Official Reports on Stranded Vietnamese Vessel </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Reports on Stranded Vietnamese Vessel </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1805145794 Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network in 
Indonesian 1200 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1805145794 </F>
<F P=104>  Jakarta Radio Republik Indonesia Network </F>
<F P=105>  Indonesian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A vessel carrying Vietnamese refugees was found 
stranded between Tanjung Keluang and the West Waringin city of 
Kumai in Central Kalimantan. Bibit Sundari, Central Kalimantan 
public relations chief, said the refugees had a wooden vessel 20 
meters wide and 60 meters long. There were 30 adults and 21 
children aboard the vessel. 
  The vessel was out of fuel and food. The boat people 
requested three [word indistinct], 200 liters of oil, 300 kg of 
rice, drinking water, and sufficient cooking oil. 
  They needed the supplies to continue their effort to reach 
Australia. 

</TEXT>

