<H3> <TI>   Ramos Signs Measure To Liberalize Banking Market </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ramos Signs Measure To Liberalize Banking Market </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1905065294 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 
19 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1905065294 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City Radio Filipinas </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Ramos has signed into law the measure 
liberalizing the entry of foreign banks into the country. In 
his speech during the signing, the president said the new law 
will trigger more efficient operation for local banks as well as 
facilitate new business and investments. Republic Act 7721 was 
also lauded by members of the banking community. Rafael 
Buenavantura, president of the Bankers' Association of the 
Philippines, said the new law is a balance between national 
interest and the economy's globalization requirement. 

</TEXT>

