<H3> <TI>   ABB Said To Order Assassination of Sison Loyalists </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ABB Said To Order Assassination of Sison Loyalists </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1805143294 Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network 
in Tagalog 0930 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1805143294 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network 
in Tagalog 0930 GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Tagalog </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Alex Boncayao Brigade [ABB] has issued a 
directive to kill the leaders of the group loyal to Jose Maria 
Sison, Communist Party of the Philippines chief. This was 
revealed earlier today by Chief Superintendent Leandro Mendoza, 
Philippine National Police [PNP] director for intelligence. 
  According to Mendoza, the fight between the ABB and Sison 
loyalists might commence any day and may trigger violence in 
Metro Manila. 
  Mendoza refused to identify who among the leaders of Sison 
loyalists are included in the hit list of the ABB. Mendoza 
added that if the killings start, the peace process maybe 
affected. 
  As of now, the PNP is monitoring the activities of the two 
groups to prevent the outbreak of violence. 
  [Begin Mendoza recording in progress] ...because this might 
escalate to a point where they will be killing each other. And 
in the process, of course, neither of the group will admit to 
the slaying. The government might be blamed for the killings. 
[end recording] 

</TEXT>

