<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A regional trial court in Quezon Province, 180 
kilometers south of Manila, has ordered the transfer of captured 
Leftist leader Wilma Tiamzon from the national police to the 
custody of a Joint Peace Committee of the Catholic Bishops' 
Conference and the National Council of Churches in the 
Philippines. The court order virtually released Tiamzon to the 
Joint Peace Committee, which named Bishop Alberto Ramento as 
Tiamzon's local guardian and who shall be charged to their 
safety and appearance in court. [sentence as heard] The 
arrangement was reached after President Ramos earlier announced 
Tiamzon's release on the recognizance of a responsible 
institution. 

</TEXT>

