<H3> <TI>   U.S. Visitor Decries `Propaganda' Against North </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S. Visitor Decries `Propaganda' Against North </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1905045794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0440 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1905045794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 19 (KCNA) -- The U.S. clamor about 
war preparations of the Korean People's Army is a lie, said John 
M. Swomley, executive director of the American Committee on 
Korea, after visiting Panmunjom at the head of a delegation of 
the committee. 
  Noting that propaganda against the Democratic People's 
Republic of Korea is going on unabated in the United States, he 
said Americans are not well informed about the existence of the 
concrete wall dividing Korea into North and South. 
  He contended that the United States should pull its forces 
and nuclear weapons out of South Korea, saying the U.S. Forces 
have not withdrawn from South Korea still today when the "Cold 
War" has come to an end. 

</TEXT>

