<H3> <TI>   U.S., ROK 17 May Military Exercises Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    U.S., ROK 17 May Military Exercises Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1905045594 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0438 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1905045594 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 19 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists on 
May 17 sent the overseas-based AWACs to the sky above South 
Korea to stage a joint air war exercise against the North with 
the puppets in the skies above Muju, Nonsan, Yoju and Yongwol, 
according to military sources. 
  The war gamble was aimed at testing the feasibility of the 
AWACs "E-3" command over combined flying corps and the accuracy 
of joint surprise strike at targets. 
  On the same day, the South Korean puppets deployed 10 
large-calibre guns, commandos, more than 100 military vehicles 
and thousands of puppet armed bandits in Paju County. 
  Meanwhile, the puppet tank groups deployed in Paju County 
fired scores of shells near the demilitarized zone of the 
military demarcation line and puppet armed helicopters launched 
support exercises for missile attack operation and ground attack 
in the sky above Yonchon County and Chorwon County, South Korean 
Kangwon Province. 

</TEXT>

