<H3> <TI>   Japan's Bid for UNSC Seat Denounced </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan's Bid for UNSC Seat Denounced </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1905050894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0454 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1905050894 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Impudent Remarks" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 19 (KCNA) -- Japanese Prime Minister 
Hata reportedly claimed again that Japan should take a permanent 
seat on the UN Security Council [UNSC]. Speaking at the plenary 
session of the House of Representatives on May 16, he said 
"calls for Japan to play its role in the new era have come from 
the United Nations." 
  His remarks are a mockery of the unbiased opinion of the 
international community which has consistently opposed Japan's 
shameless attempt to obtain a permanent seat in the UN Security 
Council. 
  Now, Japan is scheming to call back the militarist spectre 
of 
the past, crudely violating the UN Charter. 
  All the more grave is the fact that Japan is stepping up its 
nuclear armament and its conversion into a military power in an 
effort to carry this criminal scheme into effect. 
  It is only too clear that a war criminal, a nuclear 
criminal, 
cannot become a permanent member of the UN Security Council. 
  As the international community opines fairly, Japan has 
neither justification nor elementary qualification to hold a 
responsible position in the UN. 
  Japan, a criminal state which unleashed the Second World 
War, 
has yet to cleanse her dishonour as an "enemy state" stipulated 
in the UN charter, and yet to apologize for the crimes it 
committed against the Korean and other Asian nations in the past 
and make compensations for the damages. 
  Japan must clearly liquidate her crime-woven past and stop 
her nuclear armament and moves to become a military power for 
domination over Asia, instead of impudently coveting for a 
responsible position in the UN. 

</TEXT>

