<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon Sends Appeal on Japanese `Persecution' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon Sends Appeal on Japanese `Persecution' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1905052794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0459 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1905052794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 17 [dateline as received] (KNS-KCNA) -- 
Han Tok-su, chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the 
General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon), 
sent to international organisations, peace, democratic and 
solidarity organisations and prominent figures of many countries 
around the world an appeal for a solidarity movement to force 
the Japanese authorities to stop persecuting and suppressing 
Chongnyon and Korean nationals in Japan. 
  The appeal recalls that persecution and suppression of 
Koreans is openly committed in Japan and on the 25th of April 
the Japanese police searched the Osaka Prefectural headquarters 
of Chongnyon and its branch offices by letting loose scores of 
riot police vehicles and more than 1,300 policement. 
  The appeal says: 
  "It must not go unnoticed that the Japanese authorities are 
trying to justify their massive arms buildup by spreading rumors 
about `threat from North Korea' through all the propaganda 
machines and media and, furthermore, to pave the way for a 
comeback to the Korean peninsula and Asia by enacting a 
'security emergency law' and forcing constitution revision at 
any cost. 
  "The Japanese authorities, far from deeply repenting of, and 
apologizing and compensating for the colonial domination over 
Korea and the past crimes against the Korean people, are 
persecuting the Koreans in Japan, the direct victims of the 
colonial domination, and savagely suppressing the Chongnyon 
organisation that speaks for their democratic national rights 
under the groundless pretext. We sternly denounce this, 
branding it as one more crime against humanitarianism." 
  "In view of the grave situation today, we appeal to our 
friends worldwide who love justice and peace to launch a 
solidarity movement protesting the unpardonable persecution and 
suppression of Chongnyon and Korean nationals in Japan by the 
Japanese authorities and calling for its immediate halt." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

