<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Anniversary of 1980 Kwangju Incident Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Anniversary of 1980 Kwangju Incident Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Pyongyang Rally Marks Event </H4>

<F P=102> SK1805213394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1510 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1805213394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 18 (KCNA) -- A Pyongyang mass rally 
was held at the Pyongyang indoor stadium today to mark the 14th 
anniversary of the heroic Kwangju popular uprising. 
  It was attended by Pak Song-chol, Politburo member of the 
C.C. [Central Committee], the Workers' Party of Korea [WPK] and 
vice president of the DPRK, Kim Yong-sun, secretary of the C.C., 
the WPK, Chang Chol, vice-premier of the Administration Council, 
and other senior officials, 10,000 citizens and Koreans from 
abroad. 
  South Korean students and people rose up in a mass uprising 
in Kwangju on May 18, 1980, fought "martial law troops" and 
armed themselves with the weapons they wrested from the enemy 
and completely controlled and defended Kwangju city for more 
than ten days. The heroic resistance involved more than a 
million students and citizens. 
  In his speech at the rally, Kang Hyon-su, member of the 
C.C., 
the WPK and chief secretary of the Pyongyang Municipal Party 
Committee and chairman of the Pyongyang Municipal People's 
Committee, said the Kwangju popular uprising was a just 
anti-U.S., anti-fascist democratic resistance of the South 
Korean people who turned out against the U.S. imperialists' 
colonial rule and the extension of the "Yusin" fascist 
dictatorship and for the democratization of society and the 
reunification of the country and a mass armed uprising in which 
the entire citizens of Kwangju waged a death-defying resistance 
in the teeth of fascist violence. 
  The U.S. imperialists transferred 70,000 puppet troops, 150 
tanks and armored vehicles under their command to the military 
fascists to put down the uprising. 
  In some ten days, the South Korean military fascist clique 
killed more than 5,000 people and injured 14,000. 
  "Through the Kwangju popular uprising, the South Korean 
people clearly learned that U.S. imperialism is the strangler of 
independence and democracy and the chieftain of aggression and 
murder and gained at the cost of blood the lesson that no 
desires could be realised as long as the U.S. imperialist 
aggression forces remain in South Korea," said the speaker. 
  He said that with the traitor Kim Yong-sam left intact, the 
bitter grudges of the Kwangju resistance fighters cannot be 
settled and there will be nothing but confrontation and war 
between fellow countrymen. 
  The earnest desire of the participants of the Kwangju 
uprising for independence, democracy and reunification must be 
realised without fail, he added. 
  The speaker continued: 
  "As long as the U.S. Forces remain in South Korea and the 
U.S. colonial rule continues, no desire of the South Korean 
people can be realised. 
  "The United States must make a bold decision to withdraw its 
aggressor troops and nuclear weapons from South Korea in 
accordance with the trend of the times and the demand of our 
nation and approach the DPRK-USA talks with a sincere attitude 
and position for a peaceful solution to the nuclear issue on the 
Korean peninsula. 
  "It is our unshakable position to answer dialogue with 
dialogue and war with war. 
  "The United States must clearly see the indomitable will and 
stamina of our people and stop the campaign over `nuclear issue' 
aimed at stifling Korean-style socialism centred on the masses. 
  "The United States must accede to our proposal for 
establishing a new peace arrangement since the Korean Armistice 
Agreement has been reduced to a sheet of paper incapable of 
preserving peace on the Korean peninsula and the military 
armistice commission cannot perform its mission due to her 
illegalities. 
  "The South Korean students and people must wage a powerful 
mass struggle in all areas for the abolition of the `National 
Security Law' and other fascist laws and all repressive machines 
and courageously fight to overthrow the Kim Yong-sam puppet 
regime and establish a genuine independent democratic government 
of the people." 
  Representatives of various social strata also took the 
floor. 
  They all stressed that the South Korean people must 
undauntedly wage the anti-U.S. struggle for independence to 
terminate the colonial rule of the United States, achieve the 
independent and peaceful reunification of the country and 
realise what the participants of the Kwangju uprising desired. 

</TEXT>

