<H3> <TI>   Textile Pacts Extended With U.S., Norway, Canada </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Textile Pacts Extended With U.S., Norway, Canada </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1805082094 Bangkok Radio Thailand Network in English 0000 
GMT 18 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1805082094 </F>
<F P=104>  Bangkok Radio Thailand Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Thailand has extended textile agreements with the 
United States, Norway, and Canada. The extension of the 
agreements was acknowledged by the Cabinet as proposed by the 
Ministry of Commerce. 
  With the United States Thailand signed a memorandum of 
understanding on 1 April 1994 extending their bilateral textile 
agreement for another year. The agreement would automatically 
be extended for another year if the GATT textile agreement does 
not come into effect. With Norway Thailand signed agreed 
minutes extending their textile agreement for another two years 
from 1 January 1994 to 31 December 1995. 
  Thailand and Canada signed an agreed record of discussion 
extending their textile accord for another two years from 1 
January 1994 to 31 December 1995. 

</TEXT>

