<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Fifth National Assembly Session To Open 25 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fifth National Assembly Session To Open 25 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1905112594 Ho Chi Minh City SAIGON GIAI PHONG in 
Vietnamese 27 Apr 94 p 1 </F>

<F P=103> BK1905112594 </F>
<F P=104>  Ho Chi Minh City SAIGON GIAI PHONG </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by "L.C."] </F>
  [Text] The Ninth National Assembly Standing Committee 
recently decided that the Fifth National Assembly Session will 
open on 25 May and that its planned closing date will be 23 
June. 
  According to the schedule, the session will examine and pass 
six draft laws, including the draft labor code, the draft law on 
domestic investment promotion, the draft law on taxes on the 
transfer of land ownership, the draft of the (revised) law on 
military service, the draft of the revised law on people's 
council and people's committee organizations, and the draft of 
the revised law on people's council elections. The session will 
also consider a draft civil code. 
  With the draft law on the state budget in particular, the 
committee initially planned to present this legislation for 
passage at the Fifth National Assembly Session. Later the 
committee was requested by the government to ask the National 
Assembly to postpone consideration until the Sixth National 
Assembly Session, as this draft law is very important and may 
affect socioeconomic development. 
  The session will hear a government report and consider 
implementation of the resolution on practicing thrift, fighting 
wasteful spending, corruption, and smuggling. 
  The session will also include reports on the National 
Assembly Standing Committee, the Supreme People's Court, the 
Supreme People's Organ of Control, the Nationalities Council, 
and other National Assembly committees during the first six 
months of 1994. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

