<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 17 (YONHAP) -- Foreign Minister Han 
Sung-chu, currently on a tour of Southeast Asia, stopped over in 
Seoul to attend a garden party for foreign diplomats hosted by 
the president Tuesday afternoon. 
  Han, who completed the schedule at his first stop in Manila, 
will leave for his next destination, Bangkok, after the event at 
Chongwadae (presidential residence) so he can get some rest on a 
trip that also takes him to Vietnam and Indonesia. 
  Ministry officials explained that it is customary for the 
foreign minister to attend the annual party for foreign envoys 
at this time of the year. They made it clear that there was no 
urgent reason for Han to fly back home during his overseas trip. 
The minister's one-day return was scheduled long before he 
embarked on his tour and, therefore, Thursday was left free, 
they said. 

