<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 18, (YONHAP) -- Argentine Economic 
Minister Domingo Cavallo, saying that the business climate in 
his country is favorable, urged South Korean businessmen to 
invest in Argentina. 
  "Now is a good time for Korean business enterprises to 
invest 
in Argentina," Cavallo told a press conference held Tuesday at 
Hyatt Hotel in Seoul. 
  Argentina's economy is opening up speedily with 90 percent 
of 
state-run companies having been privatized, he said, adding: "In 
particular, we welcome Korean investment in automobile and 
electronics sectors." 
  Earlier in the day, Cavallo and Korean Vice Foreign Minister 
Hong Sun-yong signed an investment guarantee agreement. He also 
met with leaders of Korean business groups including Hyundai, 
Samsung, Daewoo and Lucky-Goldstar and asked them to invest more 
in the South American country. 

