<H3> <TI>   TV Networks Not Allowed To Carry 24-Hour CNN Casts </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    TV Networks Not Allowed To Carry 24-Hour CNN Casts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK1805081694 Seoul YONHAP in English 0626 GMT 18 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK1805081694 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, May 18 (YONHAP) -- The Information Ministry 
on Wednesday ruled out the possibility of permitting 
around-the-clock broadcasting by domestic cable TV networks of 
Cable News Network (CNN) programs. The ministry thus denied 
some reports that the government was studying the possibility of 
allowing CNN programs to be broadcast all day in Korea through 
domestic cable TV. 
  So Chong-hwan, director-general of the ministry's broadcast 
bureau, said the issue will not be discussed any longer as the 
present laws do not allow all-day broadcast. 
  "It is a matter to be discussed only after domestic cable TV 
takes root," said suh, referring to a government decision 
adopted at a meeting of officials from the Economic Planning 
Board and other government agencies related with trade talks 
with the United States on May 11. 
  He stressed that all-day relaying of CNN broadcast cannot be 
permitted under any circumstances as "it is feared to cause 
serious cultural problems. TV viewers will be made to understand 
international issues through American points of view. The 
broadcast, if permitted, will adversely affect the development 
of the domestic cable TV," he said. 

</TEXT>

