<F P=100> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Ministry Protests Mistreatment of Diplomat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Ministry Protests Mistreatment of Diplomat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1705083294 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 0811 GMT 17 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1705083294 </F>
<F P=104>  Moscow ITAR-TASS </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar May 17 ITAR-TASS -- The Mongolian 
Foreign Ministry has delivered a note of protest to the Russian 
envoy to Mongolia in connection with the assault on, and robbery 
of Mongolian Vice-Consul in Buriatiya Batsuur and several 
persons who accompanied him near the Ubienny mountain pass near 
the town of Gusinoozersk on May 11. 
  According to the note, the Mongols were robbed of cash, 
valuables and official documents. Batsuur suffered serious 
injuries, despite the fact that he had identified himself as a 
consular employee. 
  The Mongolian Foreign Ministry expressed the hope that the 
criminals who violated the Mongolian consular employee's 
diplomatic immunity will be identified and brought to account, 
the press-service of the Mongolian Foreign Ministry said. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

