<H3> <TI>   Japan Said Using Nuclear Issue To Expand Military </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan Said Using Nuclear Issue To Expand Military </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2005055094 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0529 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2005055094 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Crafty Ruse"--KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, May 20 (KCNA) -- Ichiro Ozawa and other 
ultra-rightists of Japan are openly making haste with the 
completion of legal preparations for military expansion 
overseas, raising a terrific hue and cry over "a security 
crisis" with regard to the "nuclear issue" of the DPRK. 
  Commenting on this, a NODONG SINMUN analyst today says: 
  Japanese Foreign Minister Koji Kakizawa stated recently that 
the government was examining "emergency legislative 
arrangements" for the reaction of the "self-defense forces" in 
"the event of contingency" on the Korean peninsula, taking issue 
with the "nuclear issue" of the DPRK. And the general director 
of the defense agency and the chief cabinet secretary also said 
that practical preparations for "security emergency legislative 
arrangements" had been completed by and large. 
  The "security crisis" advertised by the Japanese rulers is a 
sheer fiction. No one threatens or intends to attack Japan 
today. 
  Their outcries over "a security crisis" are a sophism for 
justifying their hostile policy against the DPRK and their 
scheme to stage a military comeback to Korea. 
  In actuality, the reactionary ruling circles of Japan, 
peddling the ware of "security crisis," are seeking to establish 
"an emergency system" and "a wartime mobilisation system" 
through the "security emergency legislative arrangements" 
against "an event of contingency" on the Korean peninsula and 
legally gratify their desire of military reinvasion. 
  Japan has made all military and material preparations for 
reinvasion. What remains to be done is to create a legal 
foundation allowing it. 
  In advertising "a security crisis" over the "nuclear issue" 
of the DPRK, the Japanese reactionaries also intend to prop up 
the unstable present government by sidetracking the attention of 
the Japanese people. 
  The militarists manipulated by the force of Ichiro Ozawa are 
wringing their own necks in the suicidal act of getting 
overheated in the reinvasion moves while crying for the 
establishment of "an emergency system." The Asian people are 
highly vigilant against the reinvasion moves of the Japanese 
right-wing reactionaries. 
  The Japanese reactionary ruling quarters should face the 
reality squarely and give up their foolish attempt to repeat the 
past crimes. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

