<H3> <TI>   Chongnyon's Osaka Branch Meets Japanese Media </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chongnyon's Osaka Branch Meets Japanese Media </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2005112994 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0500 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2005112994 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 18 (KNS-KCNA) [dateline as received] -- 
The Osaka prefectural headquarters of the General Association of 
Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) held a roundtable 
conversation with Japanese media on May 16. 
  Present on the occasion were the head of the local branch 
office of the Japanese JIJI press, chief editors of the Osaka 
head offices of ASAHI SHIMBUN, MAINICHI SHIMBUN, NIHON KEIZAI 
SHIMBUN and SANKEI SHIMBUN and representatives of the NHK, the 
KYODO News Service and YOMIURI SHIMBUN. 
  Speaking at the roundtable, O Hyong-chin, vice-chairman of 
the Chongnyon Central Standing Committee and chairman of the 
Osaka prefectural headquarters of Chongnyon, said the question 
of "suspected nuclear development" of the DPRK has been reported 
by Japanese media in a way contrary to facts, thereby hampering 
the solution of the nuclear issue on the Korean peninsula and, 
furthermore, the denuclearization of Northeast Asia. "The DPRK 
has neither intention nor capacity to develop nuclear weapons," 
he stressed. 
  Calling attention to the unreasonable search of the Osaka 
organization of Chongnyon by the Japanese police, assaults on 
Korean students in Japan and rampant reports and tones inciting 
the consciousness of national chauvinism, he demanded an 
immediate halt to such acts. 

</TEXT>

