<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   KCNA Reports Demonstrations in Kwangju 18 May </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KCNA Reports Demonstrations in Kwangju 18 May </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2005122494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0511 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2005122494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 20 (KCNA) -- More than 3,000 students 
and citizens out of the participants in a commemoration ceremony 
and a people's rally on the 14th anniversary of the May 18 
Kwangju popular resistance which was held in Kwangju, the city 
of resistance, on May 18 went over to a demonstration from 11:00 
at night, according to a report from Seoul. 
  The demonstrators thronged to the Kwangju and South Cholla 
Provincial branches of the "Democratic Liberal Party" and 
strongly demanded a probe into the truth behind the Kwangju 
massacre which was still kept in the dark and the punishment of 
those responsible for it. 
  They continued the demonstration till past midnight, 
fighting 
the riot police. 
  That day another group of participants in the people's rally 
mourned those who fell in the Kwangju resistance, marching in a 
candle procession toward the Kwangju railway station along 
Kumnan road, the spot of the historical resistance. 

</TEXT>

