<F P=102>   SK2005125494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1008 GMT 20 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2005125494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, May 20 (KCNA) -- The South Korean 
National Committee of Struggle for the Reinstatement of the 
Detained, wanted and dismissed workers (Chonhaetu), an 
organization embracing workers of some 40 businesses, called for 
rising general turnout in the struggle for the reinstatement of 
dismissed workers at a rally held with the attendance of some 
1,000 workers, students and citizens, according to a South 
Korean newspaper report. 
  It criticized the Kim Yong-sam regime for turning a deaf ear 
to voices of the workers across the country calling for 
reinstatement and the guarantee of their right to live. "The 
reinstatement of the dismissed workers is possible only when a 
mass struggle is waged," it said, and stressed: "Let all of us 
devote our efforts, lives and energy to the struggle for their 
reinstatement." 
  It declared that the dismissed workers in all parts of South 
Korea would enter into a tent sit-in and a hunger strike for an 
indefinite period and wage a death-defying battle till their 
demands have been met. 

</TEXT>

