<H3> <TI>   Shinseito Member Removed After Criticizing Ozawa </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Shinseito Member Removed After Criticizing Ozawa </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW1905124694 Tokyo KYODO in English 1226 GMT 19 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW1905124694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, May 19 KYODO -- A director of a key 
committee in the House of Representatives from Shinseito [Japan 
Renewal Party], a core party in the ruling coalition, was 
removed from the post after criticizing his boss, Ichiro Ozawa, 
party officials said Thursday [19 May]. 
  Koichiro Aino was replaced by Morio Kimura, another 
Shinseito 
member, as a director of the lower house steering committee, the 
officials said. 
  A senior party official said the change is a regular one. 
But the sudden change is widely regarded as punishment for 
Aino, who described the formation of a joint parliament group in 
the lower house which triggered the withdrawal of the Social 
Democratic Party (SDP) from the coalition as a blunder by Ozawa. 
  Aino's remarks angered Ozawa, the chief coalition 
strategist, 
and he later retracted them. 
  The SDP walked out of the coalition in late April after the 
abrupt formation of the Kaishin parliamentary group, excluding 
the party. The SDP's withdrawal meant Prime Minister Tsutomu 
Hata had to form a minority government for the first time in 39 
years. 

</TEXT>

