<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Banned Conferees Named </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Banned Conferees Named </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2005105594 Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network 
in Tagalog 0930 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2005105594 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City GMA-7 Radio-Television Arts Network 
in Tagalog 0930 GMT 20 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Tagalog </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] All foreigners participating in the East Timor 
Conference will be barred from entering the country. This was 
the order given by the president to the Departments of Justice 
and Foreign Affairs. 
  Ramos said that the entry of foreign nationals attending the 
conference on East Timor is inimical to national interests. 
  The eight foreigners who will be banned from entering the 
country are: Jose Ramos Horta, Carmel Budjardjo, Jose Gutierrez, 
Lim-Siou Liong, A. Perera, Maria Alkatiri, Juan Feberer, and 
Jaoa Carrascalao. They will not be given visas. Visas already 
issued will be canceled, while those foreigners already in the 
country may be deported. Only foreign exchange students will be 
allowed to attend the conference. 

</TEXT>

