<F P=100> Philippines </F>
<H3> <TI>   Claimed Parts of Spratlys To Be Developed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Claimed Parts of Spratlys To Be Developed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2005100094 Quezon City Radio Filipinas in English 0230 GMT 
20 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2005100094 </F>
<F P=104>  Quezon City Radio Filipinas </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Department of Interior and Local Government 
[DILG] will transform the mineral-rich Kalayaan [Freedom] chain 
of islands [part of Spratly Islands claimed by the Philippines] 
into one of the country's viable local government unit. The 
Kalayaan Islands is considered to be the next flash point among 
the Asian claimant nations. DILG Acting Secretary Alexander 
Aguirre said the transformation will be in line with earlier 
plans of the Cabinet Cluster "E" to attract settlers in the 
area. Aside from the Philippines, the other claimant nations 
which have already established military units in the areas 
include Malaysia, Taiwan, Vietnam, Brunei and China. 

</TEXT>

